1
00:00:06,801 --> 00:00:12,497
God helps those that help themselves.
There has to be something from your side.

2
00:00:12,767 --> 00:00:15,280
[God Helps Those Who Help Themselves]

3
00:00:15,280 --> 00:00:20,460
Very often we meet someone
in Krishna consciousness,

4
00:00:20,537 --> 00:00:27,581
and they will say that they like Krishna,
they like the devotees,

5
00:00:27,581 --> 00:00:31,789
they like Krishna, they like everything,
everything, and they accept everything.

6
00:00:32,533 --> 00:00:36,633
But then you say,
“But what about initiation?”

7
00:00:36,633 --> 00:00:43,653
and I remember, we were 
in … Kazan, that’s the city, right?

8
00:00:43,999 --> 00:00:49,689
So, and someone had been given 
the japa-mala before initiation,

9
00:00:49,689 --> 00:00:53,992
and they said, “I’ve got everything,
why do I need? I have …”, you know.

10
00:00:54,971 --> 00:00:57,051
They will make some case like that.

11
00:00:57,668 --> 00:01:01,096
Sometimes I have told them that yes,

12
00:01:01,096 --> 00:01:03,474
it’s good that you accept everything.

13
00:01:03,474 --> 00:01:07,314
You are accepting Krishna,
Krishna conception, and that’s wonderful.

14
00:01:07,699 --> 00:01:10,408
That’s what we want—varaṇa.

15
00:01:10,408 --> 00:01:15,404
Śravaṇa-daśā—hearing stage,
and then varaṇa—acceptance.

16
00:01:15,424 --> 00:01:20,634
But acceptance has to be mutual.
It’s not a one-sided affair.

17
00:01:20,956 --> 00:01:25,098
So, there is the acceptance 
from your side, that’s good.

18
00:01:25,138 --> 00:01:30,726
Then what we need is the recognition from 
the upper world of the mutual acceptance.

19
00:01:30,876 --> 00:01:33,869
That from the upper world
or the agent of the upper world

20
00:01:33,869 --> 00:01:36,670
that you have been accepted

21
00:01:36,670 --> 00:01:40,094
as sincere … what Gurudev 
would call ‘a sincere seeker’:

22
00:01:40,427 --> 00:01:43,588
“My Guru Maharaj told me, ‘Wherever 
you will meet sincere seekers,

23
00:01:43,596 --> 00:01:47,366
you will extend this
Krishna-nama to them.’”

24
00:01:47,416 --> 00:01:50,720
Krishna-prema bija-prada:
“You will give them

25
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:54,700
the seeds of Krishna-prema
through this Hari-nama.”

26
00:01:55,030 --> 00:01:59,739
So it has to [be] …
there should be this mutual acceptance.

27
00:01:59,739 --> 00:02:02,163
That’s something else to factor in.

28
00:02:02,163 --> 00:02:04,811
God helps those that help themselves.

29
00:02:04,811 --> 00:02:09,691
Something from your side
indicating your sincerity,

30
00:02:09,691 --> 00:02:13,339
your desire for a connection
with Divinity,

31
00:02:13,339 --> 00:02:17,871
your desire for some help,
some shelter, all of these things.

